Load the sample by dropwise addition and wash the cartridge with the flow-through from the sample (1 × 0.5 mL);
Desalt by passing solvent A (3 × 1 mL);
Elute the peptides by adding 1 mL of solvent B (80% CH3CN, 20% H2O, 0.1% FA);
Evaporate the eluent to dryness using SpeedVac vacuum concentrator.
Note: At this stage there should be no visible salts in the Eppendorf tube.
Pause Point: The samples can be stored at −20°C or −80°C for several months.
Re-suspend the sample in solvent A (500 μL) with sonication and fractionate into a 96 deep-well plate using HPLC (Agilent).
Add 20 μL of 20% FA to each well in a 96-well collection plate to acidify the eluting peptides.
Elute the peptides onto a capillary column (ZORBAX 300Extend-C18, 3.5 μm) and separate at a flow rate of 0.5 mL/min using the following gradient: 100% Ammonium bicarbonate (Buffer C; 10 mM) from 0–2 min, 0%–13% acetonitrile from 2–3 min, 13%–42% acetonitrile from 3–60 min, 42%–100% acetonitrile from 60–61 min, 100% acetonitrile from 61–65 min, 100%–0% acetonitrile from 65–66 min, 100% buffer C from 66–75 min, 0%–13% acetonitrile from 75–78 min, 13%–80% acetonitrile from 78–80 min, 80% acetonitrile from 80–85 min, 100% buffer C from 86–91 min, 0%–13% acetonitrile from 91–94 min, 13%–80% acetonitrile from 94–96 min, 80% acetonitrile from 96–101 min, and 80%–0% acetonitrile from 101–102 min. Use the following time-based fraction collection: 5–75 min, 96 fractions (collection mode: A1-A12, B1-B12, C1-C12, D1-D12, E1-E12, F1-F12, G1-G12, H1-H12).
Evaporate the eluent to dryness in the plate using SpeedVac vacuum concentrator.
